# Testing Guide — {{project_name}}

**Purpose**: Reference document for all developers and agents writing or
reviewing tests. Follow these conventions, patterns, and examples.

---

## Stack and Tooling

| Tool             | Purpose                                       | How to use                          |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| **cargo test**   | Unit and integration test runner              | `cargo test -p <crate>`             |
| **tokio::test**  | Async Rust tests                              | `#[tokio::test]` attribute          |
| **mockall**      | Trait-based mocking for unit tests            | `#[automock]` / `mock!` macro       |
{{#if has_network}}| **wiremock**     | HTTP mock server for outbound call testing    | `MockServer::start().await`         |
{{/if}}| **proptest**     | Property-based testing (security-critical)    | `proptest!` macro                   |
{{#if has_crypto}}| **cargo-fuzz**   | Coverage-guided fuzzing                       | `cargo fuzz run <target>`           |
{{/if}}| **assert_cmd**   | CLI integration testing                       | `Command::cargo_bin("name")`        |

**Running tests:**

```bash
# Full test suite
cargo test --workspace

# Single crate
cargo test -p {{package_name}}

# Specific test by name pattern
cargo test -p {{package_name}} test_name

# With log output
RUST_LOG=debug cargo test -- --nocapture

# Doc tests
cargo test --doc
```

